TIME_COMPLEXITY: O(2^n)
SPACE_COMPLEXITY: O(n)
APPROACH: The recursive approach works on a simple idea: to reach stair n, you could have come from either stair n-1 (took 1 step) or stair n-2 (took 2 steps) — so the total ways = ways(n-1) + ways(n-2). 
The function keeps calling itself, 
breaking the problem smaller and smaller until it hits the base case (n=0 or n=1), where it just returns 1.
 The downside is it recalculates the same values over and over, making it exponentially slow at O(2ⁿ).